# Mersenne Prime Search CPU Client

A distributed computing client for searching Mersenne prime numbers. This client allows users to contribute their CPU power to the search for these special prime numbers.

## Features

- Web-based interface for easy monitoring and control
- Multi-core CPU support for efficient processing
- Real-time statistics and progress tracking
- Configurable number of CPU cores
- Persistent configuration saving
- Automatic task distribution and management

## System Requirements

- Windows 10 or later
- 64-bit operating system
- 2GB RAM minimum
- Internet connection

## Installation

### Using the Executable

1. Download the latest release from the releases page
2. Extract the ZIP file to your desired location
3. Run `mersenne_web.exe`

## Usage

1. Launch the application
2. Access the web interface at `http://127.0.0.1:5002`
3. Enter a username (3-20 characters, alphanumeric with underscores)
4. Configure the number of CPU cores to use
5. Click "Start Processing" to begin contributing

## Monitoring

The web interface provides real-time information about:
- Current processing status
- Number of tasks completed
- Processing speed
- Running time
- Active tasks
- CPU core usage

## Configuration

The client automatically saves your configuration, including:
- Username
- Number of CPU cores to use
- Processing statistics

